videoSnippet.title: This 14-Year Old Doesn't Care Who Sits In Front of Him
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Parham Maghsoodloo vs Aydin Suleymanli
Aeroflot Open (2020), Round 8
26.2.2020.
Queen's Gambit Declined, Charousek (Petrosian) variation (D31)

1. c4 e6 2. Nc3 d5 3. d4 Be7 4. cxd5 exd5 5. Bf4 Nf6 6. e3 Bf5 7. Qb3 Nc6 8. Qxb7 Nb4 9. Rc1 O-O 10. Qxc7 Qxc7 11. Bxc7 Rfc8 12. Bf4 Ne4 13. f3 Nxc3 14. bxc3 g5 15. Bg3 a5 16. a4 Na2 17. Ra1 Nxc3 18. Ne2 Bb4 19. Kf2 Bc2 20. Nxc3 Bxc3 21. Ra2 Bb1 22. Re2 Rc4 23. Rc2 Be1+ 24. Kxe1 Rxc2 25. h4 Rac8 26. Bd6 R8c3 27. hxg5 Rb2

The 18th Aeroflot Open runs from 19-27 February 2020 in the Cosmos Hotel in Moscow. The A Open, for players rated 2550+ and talented juniors, has an €18,000 first prize, while the total prize fund for the three opens and blitz tournament is €140,000.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, plus a 30-second increment starting from move one. The event is sponsored by Aeroflot and organised by the Russian Chess Federation in cooperation with the Association of Chess Federations. Official website: acfed.ru
